Format your response in Markdown with these strict formatting rules:

1. Document Structure:
- Provide your response as a Markdown file
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 > h2 > h3)
- Include a table of contents for longer documents
- Add appropriate spacing between sections

2. Code and Technical Content:
- Indent code blocks with 4 spaces instead of backticks
- For inline code, use single quotes or italics
- Use proper indentation for nested lists
- Format file paths in italics

3. Content Formatting:
- Use bold for emphasis on important terms
- Create tables with proper column alignment
- Use numbered lists for sequential steps
- Use bullet points for unordered lists
- Include proper line breaks between sections

4. Special Elements:
- Format links as [text](mdc:url)
- Format images as ![alt text](mdc:image_url)
- Use > for blockquotes
- Use horizontal rules (---) to separate major sections

5. Financial Content Specifics:
- Format currency values consistently
- Use proper notation for percentages
- Format date ranges clearly
- Include proper attribution for financial data

6. Quality Standards:
- Maintain consistent capitalization
- Use proper punctuation
- Ensure proper list indentation
- Review output for compliance with all rules
